    ["What is a motherboard", "A motherboard is the main circuit board of a computer system. It provides electrical and logical connections for various hardware components, including the CPU, memory, storage devices, and expansion cards."],
    ["What is a power supply unit (PSU)", "A power supply unit (PSU) is a hardware component that converts alternating current (AC) power from a wall outlet to direct current (DC) power suitable for the components inside a computer. It provides the necessary electrical power to all components of the computer system."],
    ["What is a computer case", "A computer case, also known as a computer chassis or tower, is the enclosure that houses and protects the computer's internal components. It provides physical support, cooling, and access to various ports and connectors."],
    ["What is a cooling system", "A cooling system is a combination of hardware components, such as fans, heat sinks, and liquid cooling systems, that help dissipate heat generated by computer components. It prevents overheating and ensures the stable operation of the computer system."],
    ["What is a monitor", "A monitor, also known as a display or screen, is an output device that visually presents information and images generated by the computer. It allows users to view and interact with the graphical user interface (GUI) and multimedia content."],
    ["What is a keyboard", "A keyboard is an input device that allows users to enter text, commands, and other instructions into a computer. It consists of a set of keys, including alphanumeric keys, function keys, and special keys, arranged in a specific layout."],
    ["What is a mouse", "A mouse is an input device that enables users to control the movement of a cursor or pointer on a computer screen. It typically consists of buttons and a sensor that detects motion and translates it into on-screen movement."],
    ["What is a printer", "A printer is an output device that produces hard copies of digital documents or images stored on a computer. It accepts electronic data and transfers it onto paper or other physical media using various printing technologies."],
    ["What is a scanner", "A scanner is an input device that captures and converts physical documents or images into digital format. It uses optical sensors to read the content of the document or image and transfers the data to a computer for further processing or storage."],
    ["What is a network interface card ", "A network interface card (NIC) is a hardware component that enables a computer to connect to a network. It provides the necessary physical and logical interface to communicate with other devices on the network using Ethernet or wireless protocols."],
    ["What is a sound card", "A sound card, also known as an audio card, is a hardware component that processes and generates audio signals for a computer system. It provides audio input and output capabilities, enabling sound playback, recording, and multimedia applications."],
    ["What is a USB flash drive", "A USB flash drive, also known as a thumb drive or pen drive, is a portable storage device that uses flash memory to store and transfer data. It connects to a computer's USB port and provides a convenient and portable way to carry and transfer files."],
    ["What is a network router", "A network router is a hardware device that forwards data packets between computer networks. It examines the destination address of incoming packets and determines the best path for delivering the data to its intended destination."],
    ["What is a network switch", "A network switch is a hardware device that connects multiple devices, such as computers, printers, and servers, within a local area network (LAN). It enables devices to communicate with each other by forwarding data packets to the appropriate destination."],
    ["What is a modem", "A modem is a hardware device that converts digital signals from a computer into analog signals that can be transmitted over telephone lines or other communication channels. It enables computers to connect to the internet or other remote networks."],
    ["What is a wireless router", "A wireless router is a networking device that combines the functions of a network router and a wireless access point. It allows devices to connect to a wired or wireless network and provides internet connectivity and local network access."],
    ["What is a digital camera", "A digital camera is a device that captures and stores digital images and videos. It uses an image sensor to convert optical images into digital data, which can be stored on memory cards or transferred to a computer for further processing or sharing."],
    ["What is a barcode scanner", "A barcode scanner is a hardware device that reads and decodes barcode symbols. It uses optical sensors or lasers to capture the barcode image and convert it into a digital format that can be interpreted and processed by a computer."],
    ["What is a touchpad", "A touchpad, also known as a trackpad, is a pointing device commonly found on laptops and some desktop keyboards. It allows users to control the cursor or pointer on the screen by moving their fingers across the touch-sensitive surface."],
    ["What is a webcam", "A webcam is a video camera that captures and streams live video or video recordings over a computer network. It is commonly used for video conferencing, online meetings, live streaming, and video chatting."],
    ["What is a barcode printer", "A barcode printer is a hardware device that prints barcode labels or tags. It receives data from a computer or other input source and uses thermal or ink-based printing technology to produce the barcode images on labels or adhesive tags."],
    ["What is a biometric scanner", "A biometric scanner is a hardware device that captures and analyzes biometric data, such as fingerprints, facial features, or iris patterns. It is used for biometric authentication and identification purposes, providing a secure and convenient way to verify an individual's identity."],
    ["What is a digital projector", "A digital projector is a device that projects and displays digital images or video onto a larger screen or surface. It uses light sources and lenses to magnify and project the image, allowing for large-scale presentations or multimedia experiences."],
    ["What is a network firewall", "A network firewall is a hardware or software-based security device that monitors and controls incoming and outgoing network traffic. It acts as a barrier between an internal network and external networks, filtering and blocking unauthorized access or malicious activities."],
    ["What is a network repeater", "A network repeater, also known as a signal booster, is a hardware device that amplifies and retransmits network signals to extend the range and coverage of a network. It is used to overcome signal loss or degradation over long distances or in areas with weak network signals."],
    ["What is an external hard drive", "An external hard drive is a portable storage device that connects to a computer via USB, Thunderbolt, or other interfaces. It provides additional storage capacity and allows for easy data transfer and backup without opening the computer's case."],
    ["What is a virtual reality headset", "A virtual reality (VR) headset is a wearable device that immerses users in virtual reality environments or experiences. It typically consists of a head-mounted display (HMD), sensors, and audio components to provide a 3D interactive experience."],
    ["What is a smartwatch", "A smartwatch is a wearable device that integrates with a smartphone or other mobile devices to provide additional features and functionalities. It typically includes a display, sensors, and wireless connectivity, allowing users to receive notifications, track fitness activities, and interact with apps."],
    ["What is a network attached storage device", "A network-attached storage (NAS) device is a dedicated storage device or server that provides file-level data storage and access to multiple clients over a network. It offers centralized storage management and file sharing capabilities."],
    ["What is a Bluetooth speaker", "A Bluetooth speaker is a wireless audio device that connects to other devices, such as smartphones, tablets, or computers, using Bluetooth technology. It allows for wireless audio streaming and playback, providing a portable and convenient way to listen to music or other audio content."],
    ["What is a gaming console", "A gaming console is a specialized computer system designed primarily for playing video games. It typically includes a console unit, controllers, and connections to a display device, allowing users to play games with enhanced graphics and interactive features."],
    ["What is a network attached printer", "A network-attached printer is a printer device that connects directly to a computer network, allowing multiple users to send print jobs to the printer over the network. It eliminates the need for individual connections to each computer and enables centralized printing management."],
    ["What is a tablet computer", "A tablet computer, or simply tablet, is a portable computing device with a touchscreen display and mobile operating system. It provides functionality similar to a laptop or smartphone but with a larger display and touch-based interaction."],
    ["What is a network attached video recorder", "A network-attached video recorder (NVR) is a device that captures, records, and stores video footage from IP cameras or network video streams. It provides centralized video surveillance management and storage capabilities for security and monitoring purposes."],
    ["What is a fitness tracker", "A fitness tracker, also known as an activity tracker or fitness band, is a wearable device that monitors and tracks fitness-related metrics, such as steps taken, distance traveled, heart rate, and calories burned. It provides feedback and motivation for physical activities and fitness goals."],
    ["What is a digital audio workstation ", "A digital audio workstation (DAW) is a software or hardware-based system used for recording, editing, and producing digital audio. It provides tools and features for multitrack recording, MIDI sequencing, audio editing, and mixing for music production or audio engineering."],
